Adding the configuration component from Via 3

This is in use in Via 3, Via and LMS. This will be in use in the
upcoming Via HTML.
Removing no-cover comments from pre-split

Add a value to the good parameter list to allow ad-hoc feature flags

This is so we don't have to edit this every time there is something new
Added client classes from LMS
Add a helpers for expiry times
Add classes for creating JWT based tokens

Add new secure URL signing routines

We really should have taken 5 minutes to discuss how we were going to use
these, but in the end we've come down on the side of signing the entire
URL. This meant the existing stuff wasn't actually very convenient for that.

This packs all the goods into one routine.
Remove the old URL token routines
Fix a timezoneless date in the tests
Use ViaSecureURL to sign urls on ViaClient
Add classes for generating verifiable but arbitrary tokens
Add cookie helper methods for creating secure cookies
Move to fixed length hash based signatures for URLs
Use Blake2b hash and base 64 to reduce the length from 204 chars to 150
Explain the use of "h" instead of "url_hash" or something more descriptive

A very indirect port of the code in Via 3 used for ViaHTML linking

This extends the capability of the client to be able to talk to
ViaHTML as well as Via 3.
Pre-emptively add slashes to prevent ViaHTML redirects for bare hostnames
Add SameSite=None and Secure to cookies to allow them in iframes
Pass through the secure setting to the parent constructor

Add options to surpress adding in defaults

This allows us to extract the config as provided by the client without
any additional values they didn't send. This means we can check if they
sent any at all.
Add blocked_for param for checkmate blocked pages
Disable URL signing for viahtml
Remove un-used cookie and nonce work

Make LMS mode optional

Make the `via.client.requestConfigFromFrame.*` options, which put the
client into "LMS mode", optional.

LMS will pass these two options itself to `ViaClient.url_for()`'s
`options` argument.

This is needed for when Via 3 is being run in a non-LMS context. In that
context we don't want the client to receive the `requestConfigFromFrame`
options.
Replay cookiecutter to add support for Python 3.7, 3.8 and 3.9
Adding Python classifiers
Update the cookie cutter template
Remove the unused replay script
Remove reference to Via 3
Remove support for Python <3.8
Remove local install python in favour of hdev and fix tests

Add `ignoreOtherConfiguration` to the `hypothesisConfig`

Related to https://github.com/hypothesis/viahtml/pull/192

On the above PR viahtml make the `window.hypothesisConfig`
non-configurable and non-writable.

In addition to the above, we have added an `ignoreOtherConfiguration` to
disregard other (JSON or non-JSON) configurations and prevent options to
be merged.

Whitelist `ignoreOtherConfiguration` option for the client

Pass this nwe option, `ignoreOtherConfiguration`, to the client.

Lint fix
Add max_age arg to ViaSecureURL.create()

Allow "contentProvider" flag to be passed through

This lets LMS set the content provider with config

Apply updates from cookiecutter

Upgrade to the latest Python patch versions

Python 3.8.9 doesn't work on Apple Silicon so this upgrade is necessary to get
the development environment working on newer MacBooks. Plus it's good to keep
up to date with patch versions anyway.

The upgrade was done by changing the Python version numbers in the
`cookiecutter.json` file then running `make template`. It only changes a
couple of files because most places only specify the major and minor
version not the patch (`Makefile`, GitHub Actions workflows, etc).

Pin to tox<4

Pin to tox<4 to avoid breakage caused by tox 4.0.0 backwards-incompatibilities.

See https://github.com/hypothesis/cookiecutter-pyapp-test/pull/6 for details.
Apply updates from cookiecutter

Include hardcoded outputs on token tests

This will make it easier to validate the change to another JWT library.

Replace PyJWT by python-jose

python-jose offers JWE functionality that we want to use and we also
already use it on the LMS project.

Secret AES encryption helper

Allows to encrypt dictionaries using AES and encode both the cipher text
and IV in a base64 encoded string.

Take headers in url_for

Take an optional `headers` parameters which wild be sent AES encoded
over the wire to Via.
Rename SecureSecrets to Encryption

Switch over JWEs

Instead of our own mix of base64,AES,iv... just use JWE for the same
functionality.

Insert __copyright_year into cookiecutter.json

This is needed to prevent the cookiecutter from updating the copyright year in
the LICENSE file to the current year every new year. See:

https://github.com/hypothesis/cookiecutters/pull/105

Insert "pypi": "yes" into cookiecutter.json

This is needed to prevent the cookiecutter from removing the PyPI support from
this project now that PyPI is optional. See:

https://github.com/hypothesis/cookiecutters/pull/104
